        <h2>Why Traditional Meditation Apps Fail ADHD Users</h2>
        <p>Most popular meditation apps are actively hostile to neurodivergent focus. They are packed with daily streaks, push notifications, social leaderboards, and complex home screens. If you forget to meditate for a day, you lose your "streak," triggering rejection sensitive dysphoria (RSD) and making you want to abandon the app entirely.</p>
        <p>Furthermore, many apps force you to listen to guided vocal tracks. For someone with ADHD, listening to someone speak can feel like a chore or a podcast, completely ruining the opportunity to disconnect.</p>

